text_answer.content: I don't think it is appropriate to have 3rd graders in school. reading about a museum that shows only things about penises.  The word, "bad" under Context Clues is not challenging enough for 3rd grade students.  Regarding bias, a museum about "bad art" indicates that art can be judged objectively; when, in fact, art can only be judged "subjectively as beauty is in the eye of the beholder.  I don't think it is a good message to send to young children that there is good and bad art.  This whole story seems like a train wreck to me.
